# DLe ‚Äî Description Logic (Extended)
# Synthetic parser regression document.
# This file intentionally avoids enterprise architecture terminology while exercising
# the DLe syntax features used by the original foundation model.

@prefix : <http://example.org/wildlife-test#>

############################################################
# Domain-level grouping and modeled concepts
############################################################

Domain ‚äë ‚ä§
WildlifeConcept ‚äë ‚ä§

AnimalDomain ‚äë Domain
HabitatDomain ‚äë Domain
ResearchDomain ‚äë Domain
TaxonomyDomain ‚äë Domain

Animal ‚äë WildlifeConcept
Species ‚äë WildlifeConcept
Taxon ‚äë WildlifeConcept
Habitat ‚äë WildlifeConcept
Region ‚äë WildlifeConcept
Researcher ‚äë WildlifeConcept
ResearchTeam ‚äë WildlifeConcept
Observation ‚äë WildlifeConcept
SurveyRoute ‚äë WildlifeConcept

@db Animal
@db Species
@db Taxon
@db Habitat
@db Region
@db Researcher
@db ResearchTeam
@db Observation
@db SurveyRoute

@doc WildlifeConcept "Root class for modeled wildlife reserve concepts."
@doc Domain "Grouping class for broad wildlife reserve subject areas."
@doc Animal "Individual animal tracked or observed in the reserve."
@doc Species "Biological species represented in the reserve model."
@doc Habitat "Ecological habitat or biome."
@doc Region "Geographic region or named area in the reserve."
@doc Observation "Recorded wildlife observation."

############################################################
# Generic relationship and attribute roots
############################################################

‚àÉrelationship.‚ä§ ‚äë WildlifeConcept ‚®Ü Domain
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄrelationship.(WildlifeConcept ‚®Ü Domain)
@label relationship "Relationship"
@doc relationship "Generic relationship between modeled wildlife concepts or domains; specialized by domain-specific relationship types."

‚àÉattribute.‚ä§ ‚äë WildlifeConcept ‚äî RelationshipStatement
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄattribute.(xsd:boolean ‚äî xsd:integer ‚äî xsd:decimal ‚äî xsd:string ‚äî xsd:dateTime ‚äî xsd:date)
@doc attribute "A scalar attribute belonging to a wildlife concept or to an asserted relationship."

RelationshipStatement ‚äë rdfs:Proposition
@doc RelationshipStatement "A proposition whose described triple is asserted in the model. The predicate is a relationship type. Used to attach attributes or metadata to a relationship."

‚àÉstatementRelationship.‚ä§ ‚äë RelationshipStatement
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄstatementRelationship.rdf:Property
@doc statementRelationship "The predicate resource in a triple."

calculatedValue ‚äë attribute
@label calculatedValue "Calculated"
@doc calculatedValue "Subproperties of this are system-calculated values; this property is not intended for direct use."

calculatedNumber ‚äë calculatedValue
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄcalculatedNumber.(xsd:integer ‚äî xsd:decimal)
@label calculatedNumber "Calculated Number"
@doc calculatedNumber "Subproperties of this are numeric calculated values; this property is not intended for direct use."

calculatedList ‚äë calculatedValue
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄcalculatedList.xsd:string
@label calculatedList "Calculated List"
@doc calculatedList "Subproperties of this are calculated string values selected from a model-defined list of enumerated terms."

############################################################
# Domain assignment
############################################################

‚àÉinDomain.‚ä§ ‚äë WildlifeConcept
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.Domain
‚â§1 inDomain.‚ä§
@db inDomain "domain_id"
@label inDomain "In Domain"
@doc inDomain "Primary subject grouping for a modeled wildlife concept."

Animal ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.AnimalDomain
Species ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.TaxonomyDomain
Taxon ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.TaxonomyDomain
Habitat ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.HabitatDomain
Region ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.HabitatDomain
Researcher ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.ResearchDomain
ResearchTeam ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.ResearchDomain
Observation ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.ResearchDomain
SurveyRoute ‚äë ‚àÄinDomain.ResearchDomain

WildlifeConcept ‚â° (‚àÉinDomain.Domain) ‚äì (‚àÉname.xsd:string) ‚äì (=1 id.xsd:string)

############################################################
# Hierarchy and transitive closure
############################################################

locatedIn ‚äë relationship
‚àÉlocatedIn.‚ä§ ‚äë Habitat ‚äî Region ‚äî Observation
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄlocatedIn.(Habitat ‚äî Region)
‚â§1 locatedIn.‚ä§
@db locatedIn "located_in"
@label locatedIn "Located In"
@doc locatedIn "Immediate geographic containment. This is instance-level location containment, not rdfs:subClassOf semantics."

locatedIn ‚äë containedIn
Trans(containedIn)
contains ‚â° locatedIn‚Åª
containsTransitively ‚â° containedIn‚Åª

partOfTaxon ‚äë relationship
‚àÉpartOfTaxon.‚ä§ ‚äë Taxon
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄpartOfTaxon.Taxon
‚â§1 partOfTaxon.‚ä§
@db partOfTaxon "part_of_taxon"
@label partOfTaxon "Part Of Taxon"
@doc partOfTaxon "Immediate taxonomic containment, such as species within genus or genus within family."

partOfTaxon ‚äë broaderTaxon
Trans(broaderTaxon)
hasTaxonPart ‚â° partOfTaxon‚Åª
narrowerTaxon ‚â° broaderTaxon‚Åª

############################################################
# Relationships
############################################################

belongsToSpecies ‚äë relationship
‚àÉbelongsToSpecies.‚ä§ ‚äë Animal
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄbelongsToSpecies.Species
‚â§1 belongsToSpecies.‚ä§
@db belongsToSpecies "belongs_to_species"
@label belongsToSpecies "Belongs To Species"
@doc belongsToSpecies "Species classification of an individual animal."

inhabits ‚äë relationship
‚àÉinhabits.‚ä§ ‚äë Animal ‚äî Species
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄinhabits.Habitat
@db inhabits
@label inhabits "Inhabits"
@doc inhabits "Habitat normally used by an animal or species."

studies ‚äë relationship
‚àÉstudies.‚ä§ ‚äë Researcher
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄstudies.(Animal ‚äî Species ‚äî Habitat)
@db studies
@label studies "Studies"
@doc studies "Research relationship from a researcher to an animal, species, or habitat."

memberOf ‚äë relationship
‚àÉmemberOf.‚ä§ ‚äë Researcher
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄmemberOf.ResearchTeam
@db memberOf "member_of"
@label memberOf "Member Of"
@doc memberOf "Research team membership."

recordsAnimal ‚äë relationship
‚àÉrecordsAnimal.‚ä§ ‚äë Observation
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄrecordsAnimal.Animal
@db recordsAnimal "records_animal"
@label recordsAnimal "Records Animal"
@doc recordsAnimal "Animal recorded by an observation."

followsRoute ‚äë relationship
‚àÉfollowsRoute.‚ä§ ‚äë Observation
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄfollowsRoute.SurveyRoute
@db followsRoute "follows_route"
@label followsRoute "Follows Route"
@doc followsRoute "Survey route followed when making an observation."

hasResponsibilityRelation ‚äë relationship
‚àÉhasResponsibilityRelation.‚ä§ ‚äë Researcher
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄhasResponsibilityRelation.(Animal ‚äî Species ‚äî Habitat ‚äî SurveyRoute)
@db hasResponsibilityRelation "Has Responsibility"
@label hasResponsibilityRelation "Has Responsibility"
@doc hasResponsibilityRelation "General responsibility relation; specialized by more precise responsibility types."

monitors ‚äë hasResponsibilityRelation
curates ‚äë hasResponsibilityRelation
leadsSurveyFor ‚äë hasResponsibilityRelation
monitors ‚äì curates ‚äë ‚ä•
monitors ‚äì leadsSurveyFor ‚äë ‚ä•
curates ‚äì leadsSurveyFor ‚äë ‚ä•
@doc monitors "Researcher monitors an animal, species, habitat, or route."
@doc curates "Researcher curates data for an animal, species, habitat, or route."
@doc leadsSurveyFor "Researcher leads surveys for an animal, species, habitat, or route."

############################################################
# Role chains and inferred relationships
############################################################

belongsToSpecies ‚àò inhabits ‚äë speciesHabitat
@doc speciesHabitat "Habitat inferred for an animal through the habitat associated with its species."

recordsAnimal ‚àò belongsToSpecies ‚äë recordsSpecies
@doc recordsSpecies "Species inferred for an observation through the animal it records."

locatedIn ‚àò containedIn ‚äë locatedInWiderRegion
@doc locatedInWiderRegion "Wider geographic region inferred through location containment."

containedIn ‚àò monitors‚Åª ‚äë monitoredRegionBy
@doc monitoredRegionBy "Researcher inferred to monitor a wider region through responsibility for a contained location."

############################################################
# Inverses named for convenience
############################################################

studiedBy ‚â° studies‚Åª
hasMember ‚â° memberOf‚Åª
recordedBy ‚â° recordsAnimal‚Åª
responsibilityOf ‚â° hasResponsibilityRelation‚Åª

locatedIn ‚àò locatedIn‚Åª ‚äë neighboringPlace
Irref(neighboringPlace)

############################################################
# Basic attributes and identifiers
############################################################

‚àÉname.‚ä§ ‚äë WildlifeConcept
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄname.xsd:string
WildlifeConcept ‚äë ‚àÉname.xsd:string
‚â§1 name.‚ä§
@db name
@label name "Name"
@doc name "Unique display name for a wildlife concept."

# `matches` references the OWL xsd:pattern facet. `key()` references owl:hasKey.
‚àÉid.‚ä§ ‚äë WildlifeConcept
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄid.[xsd:string ‚äì [matches "[A-Z]{3}-[0-9]{6}"]]
WildlifeConcept ‚äë (=1 id.xsd:string)
‚â§1 id.‚ä§
WildlifeConcept ‚äë key(id)
@db id
@storage id "triplestore.subject"
@doc id "Opaque unique identifier for a modeled wildlife concept."

tagId ‚äë attribute
‚àÉtagId.‚ä§ ‚äë Animal
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄtagId.xsd:string
‚â§1 tagId.‚ä§
Animal ‚äë key(tagId)
@db tagId "tag_id"
@label tagId "Tag ID"
@storage tagId "tracking.tag"
@doc tagId "Field tag or tracking device identifier."

description ‚äë attribute
‚àÉdescription.‚ä§ ‚äë WildlifeConcept
‚ä§ ‚äë ‚àÄdescription.xsd:string
‚â§1 description.‚ä§
@db description
@label description "Description"
@doc description "Concise description of a wildlife concept."

